      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Wireless and Witless,'' by Sharon White Taylor (Op-Ed, July 5):</p>
        <p>In keeping with recent laws about headgear for cyclists and bikers, how about legislation requiring a plastic, see-through hood -- with air holes, of course -- for cell phone users who call in public places?</p>
        <p>Such a device would serve to muffle noisy talk, open up all sorts of possibilities for creative design and marketing and, considering the preparation needed for donning, just possibly might encourage some sensitivity to others.</p>
        <p>EMILY GOLDBERG  Floral Park, N.Y., July 6, 2000</p>
      </block>
